    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Montreal</placeName>
                <date>24th June 1866</date>.</p>
            <p>The <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir,</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Having heard of <lb/> your recent absence from
                    <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName><lb/> I did not send you any account of<lb/>
                the celebration of my son's Minyan<lb/> especially as some had been furnished<lb/>
                the <placeName>New York</placeName> papers. I do not know<lb/> indeed whether such a
                celebration<lb/> - always pretty much the same thing,<lb/> its history always
                repeating itself — deserves<lb/> place in a monthly — there was one<lb/> point about
                it worthy of notice, the<lb/> handsome behavior of the congregation.<lb/> As you
                know, we are not a large body<lb/> but my son was presented with a<lb/> very nice
                address (of which I will endeavor<lb/> to enclose you a copy) a valuable</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>gold watch, and a Saving's Bank<lb/> book with one hundred dollars paid on<lb/> to
                his Credit. The celebration was in<lb/> every respect a pleasant one. The<lb/>
                <add>בר חנוך</add> of course read the whole of<lb/> the <add>דרשה</add> the
                    <add>אמור</add> &amp; the <add>הפטרה</add>, and<lb/> was addressed by me
                thereafter. At<lb/> the breakfast held at my house also<lb/> which was crowded the
                presentation<lb/> took place, several toasts with<lb/> some good speaking followed
                &amp;c &amp;c &amp;c &amp;c</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">When is the Jewish<lb/> College going into operation. Would<lb/> it
                not be well to create at first<lb/> simply a Faculty of Theology, and<lb/> after
                having obtained a charter for<lb/> your college, affiliate it to one or<lb/> more
                universities in order to obtain<lb/> the advantage of their arts courses.<lb/> I am
                afraid if too much is tried,<lb/> failure will follow — If I have time<lb/> I will
                address you in the Occident</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>—though this is scarcely necessary, the<lb/> matter being in good hands.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Can't you get a good man<lb/> for <placeName>Charleston</placeName>,
                a proper, <hi rend="underline">strong</hi> man<lb/> would now check Reform
                movements<lb/> of the old stamp for the next quarter<lb/> of a century. There is a
                great want<lb/> of good Portuguese Hazanim. I hope<lb/> the projected college will
                turn out a<lb/> few.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Do you receive the Hebrew<lb/> periodicals <add>המגיד</add> or
                    <add>המבשר</add> — I would<lb/> like to see them regularly, and would<lb/>
                subscribe if I knew where. Should<lb/> you get them &amp; not care to keep<lb/>
                them, you could let me have<lb/> them occasionally.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Sarah Joseph</persName> told me when<lb/> writing to
                inquire what she is indebted<lb/> for the Bible. <persName>Mrs. De Sola</persName>
                unites<lb/> in kind regards — I am yours truly.<lb/>
                <persName role="author">Abraham de Sola</persName></p>
        </body>
